SIMPLE: oppress
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oppress
<hw>Op*press"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Oppressed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Oppressing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>oppresser</ets>, LL. <ets>oppressare</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>oppressus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>opprimere</ets>; <ets>ob</ets> (see
<er>Ob-</er>) + <ets>premere</ets> to press. See <er>Press</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To impose excessive burdens upon; to overload; hence,
to treat with unjust rigor or with cruelty.</def>
<rj><au>Wyclif.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For thee, <qex>oppress⟦egrave⟧d</qex> king, am I cast down.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Behold the kings of the earth; how they <qex>oppress</qex>⟦br⟧
Thy chosen!</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To ravish; to violate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To put down; to crush out; to suppress.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mutiny he there hastes to <qex>oppress</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To produce a sensation of weight in (some part of
the body); <as>as, my lungs are <ex>oppressed</ex> by the damp air;
excess of food <ex>oppresses</ex> the stomach</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>oppressed</ent>⟦br⟧
